         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><note>i</note>: [In the name of Christ]: in this tomb lies the body of Speratus, son of Petrus, [of good memory]. He lived in this world more or less 40 years. 
               He departed from this world in the six thousandth 512th year, 
               second indiction, in the month November. May he have rest eternal and possess life eternal. Amen, Amen, Amen.</p>
            <p><note>ii</note>: . . . ] such as [my grief. Pray] for me 
               as the Apostle James said: pray to Christ for one another so that you may be saved. May he have rest eternal and may he preserve life eternal with the saints and all the elect. Amen</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>ii.2-3: see Epistle of James, at <ref target="http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0031.tlg020.perseus-lat1:5.16">Perseus</ref>.</p>
